# VulkanDesktop — per-draw data & descriptors

Locked policy: `Docs/EngineArchitecture.md` §5.3, `VulkanDesktop/RenderCore/Vk_DescriptorPolicy.h`, `Docs/Archived/plans/descriptor-strategy_Plan.md`.

## Per-draw `mat4` model (and similar)

- **Do not** patch a **shared** per-frame `UNIFORM_BUFFER` (e.g. `GpuCameraData.model`) between multiple `vkCmdDraw*` calls that reuse the **same** bound descriptor set. Later draws may all see the **last** CPU write.
- **Do** use one of:
  - **`UNIFORM_BUFFER_DYNAMIC`** — one slab, distinct `dynamicOffset` per draw (Set 2; **demo path** in `TriangleVertex.vert`).
  - **Push constants** — `mat4` model still valid per policy for other pipelines.
- When a demo looks wrong (meshes stacked): check **transform delivery** first, not only wider entity spacing in SoA.

## Record path boundaries

- **Target:** `RecordScenePass` consumes **`Gfx_DrawInstance` only** (+ resource table resolve). Per-instance data via `myInstanceDataOffset` into an instance slab (§4.4).
- **Today:** transforms written in `FillInstanceSlab` from SoA; record binds Set 2 with `myInstanceDataOffset` only.

## Multi-mesh / batching

- Prefer **bind Set 0 / Set 1 once per material batch**; per draw: push constants + VB/IB only (§5.2).
- Set 0 texture bound only to **material 0** at init is demo-only — wire **Set 1** before claiming multi-material done.

## Shader / C++ contract

- Changing UBO layout or push ranges requires **same change set**: `GpuCameraData`, `TriangleVertex.vert`, `CreateGfxPipeline` layout, SPIR-V rebuild, and `EngineArchitecture.md` §5.3 note (see `docs-roadmap-arch-sync.mdc`).
